								<div id="padding"><div id="unique-entry-id-77" class="blog-entry"><h1 class="blog-entry-title"><a href="files/86918877c3e73ffbb74b95bc78a4e474-77.php" class="blog-permalink">GCC 12.1.0 buid on macOS 12 Monterey (x86-64)</a></h1><div class="blog-entry-date">2022-05-11 Filed in: <span class="blog-entry-category"><a href="files/category-compiler.php">Compiler</a></span></div><div class="blog-entry-body">GNAT (FSF) ~ GCC 12.1.0, X86_64 build.<br /><br />Compilers included: Ada, C, C++.<br /><br />Available on <a href="https://github.com/simonjwright/distributing-gcc" target="_blank" title="Distributing GNAT (FSF) on Mac systems">Simon&rsquo;s GitHub</a>, and soon through ALIRE<br /><ul class="disc"><li>See the release page  <a href="https://github.com/simonjwright/distributing-gcc/releases/tag/gcc-12.1.0-x86_64" target="_blank" title="GCC 12.1.0 x86-64">GCC 12.1.0 built on MacOS X El Capitan (10.11, Darwin 15), with Xcode 8.2.1</a></li></ul><br />Also runs on macOS versions up to at least Monterey (12, Darwin 21)<br /><span class="blog-read-more"><a href="files/86918877c3e73ffbb74b95bc78a4e474-77.php"> Read More…</a></span><p class="blog-entry-tags">Tags: <a href="files/tag-gcc.php" title="GCC" rel="tag">GCC</a>,<a href="files/tag-macos.php" title="MacOS" rel="tag">MacOS</a></p></div></div><div id="unique-entry-id-72" class="blog-entry"><h1 class="blog-entry-title"><a href="files/5f7fe5c25ae16f0f5f9013d903605262-72.php" class="blog-permalink">New heading for Thematics</a></h1><div class="blog-entry-date">2022-05-06 Filed in: <span class="blog-entry-category"><a href="files/category-ada-forge.php">Ada Forge</a></span></div><div class="blog-entry-body">Thematics about designing or using Ada Software Libraries<br /><br />Interested ? <br /><br /><h4>Contribute to the MD page on our GitHub</h4><br /><span style="color:#000000;">It is back on a MarkDown formatted page on </span><span style="color:#000000;"><a href="https://github.com/AdaForge/Thematics" target="_blank" title="MD Wiki page">AdaForge&rsquo;s GitHub</a></span><span style="color:#000000;">.<br />So you can collaborate easily.<br /></span><span class="blog-read-more"><a href="files/5f7fe5c25ae16f0f5f9013d903605262-72.php"> Read More…</a></span></div></div><div id="unique-entry-id-73" class="blog-entry"><h1 class="blog-entry-title"><a href="files/2847bb9ddc6e41cea218b16362069009-73.php" class="blog-permalink">Added RTFM shortcuts</a></h1><div class="blog-entry-date">2022-05-06 Filed in: <span class="blog-entry-category"><a href="files/category-ada-forge.php">Ada Forge</a></span></div><div class="blog-entry-body"><span style="color:#000000;">One place to go, AdaForge<br />and every thing is on hand!<br /><br />We&rsquo;ve put RTFM direct links on the right side-bar of the </span><span style="color:#000000;"><a href="../" title="Home">home page</a></span><span style="color:#000000;"><br /></span><span class="blog-read-more"><a href="files/2847bb9ddc6e41cea218b16362069009-73.php"> Read More…</a></span><p class="blog-entry-tags">Tags: <a href="files/tag-rtfm.php" title="RTFM" rel="tag">RTFM</a></p></div></div><div id="unique-entry-id-74" class="blog-entry"><h1 class="blog-entry-title"><a href="files/68aa6fddb835802220ba9787c9057eee-74.php" class="blog-permalink">Ada for VS Code 23.0.6 released!</a></h1><div class="blog-entry-date">2022-05-04 Filed in: <span class="blog-entry-category"><a href="files/category-tools.php">Tools</a></span></div><div class="blog-entry-body"><span style="color:#000000;"><br />Impressive </span><span style="color:#000000;"><a href="https://github.com/AdaCore/ada_language_server" target="_blank" title="Ada Language Server">Ada source code plugin</a></span><span style="color:#000000;"> for popular VS Code - </span><span style="color:#000000;"><a href="https://code.visualstudio.com/" target="_blank" title="Visual Studio Code">Microsoft Visual Studio Code editor.</a></span><span style="color:#000000;"><br /><br />Current features:<br /></span><ul class="disc"><li><span style="color:#000000;">GNAT project files support.</span></li><li><span style="color:#000000;">Code completion for names, keywords, aggregates, etc.</span></li><li><span style="color:#000000;">Code navigation, such as Go to Definition/Declaration, Find All References, Call Hierarchies, etc.</span></li><li><span style="color:#000000;">Code refactoring like insert named associations, auto-add with-clauses.</span></li><li><span style="color:#000000;">Document/Workspace symbol search.</span></li><li><span style="color:#000000;">Code folding and formatting.</span></li></ul><span style="color:#000000;"><br /><br />Great job </span><span style="font:12px AppleColorEmoji; color:#000000;">🤩🤩🤩🤩🤩🤩</span><span style="color:#000000;"> done by Maxim Reznik, Anthony Leonardo Gracio, Nicolas Setton, Adrien Boulanger, João Azevedo, Vadim Godunko & Al,  for  implementing the Microsoft </span><span style="color:#000000;"><a href="https://microsoft.github.io/language-server-protocol/" title="Microsoft Language Server Protocol">Language Server Protocol</a></span><span style="color:#000000;"> for Ada/SPARK.<br /><br />Great thanks to </span><span style="color:#000000;"><a href="https://www.adacore.com" target="_blank" title="AdaCore">Adacore</a></span><span style="color:#000000;"> for their commitment to publish it as Open Source Software on GitHub </span><span style="font:12px AppleColorEmoji; color:#000000;">😎</span><span style="color:#000000;"> <br /></span><span class="blog-read-more"><a href="files/68aa6fddb835802220ba9787c9057eee-74.php"> Read More…</a></span><p class="blog-entry-tags">Tags: <a href="files/tag-sources-editor.php" title="Sources Editor" rel="tag">Sources Editor</a></p></div></div><div id="unique-entry-id-71" class="blog-entry"><h1 class="blog-entry-title"><a href="files/606f2c0aadf7b34fb41e630e74242e2a-71.php" class="blog-permalink">New HOW-TO about choosing and inserting your software license</a></h1><div class="blog-entry-date">2022-04-30 Filed in: <span class="blog-entry-category"><a href="files/category-license.php">License</a></span></div><div class="blog-entry-body">You will find a very clever way to <strong>handle the license bla-bla</strong> <span style="font:12px AppleColorEmoji; ">🥸</span><br /><br /><h2>Rush to our <a href="../OtherResources/OSI-Licenses/" title="OSI Licenses">FOSS Licenses</a> page </h2><br /><span class="blog-read-more"><a href="files/606f2c0aadf7b34fb41e630e74242e2a-71.php"> Read More…</a></span></div></div><div id="unique-entry-id-69" class="blog-entry"><h1 class="blog-entry-title"><a href="files/24b816fa2b7025a7192910a635992334-69.php" class="blog-permalink">GtkAda contributions v3.9</a></h1><div class="blog-entry-date">2022-04-17 Filed in: <span class="blog-entry-category"><a href="files/category-framework.php">Framework</a></span></div><div class="blog-entry-body"><br />Changes to the version 3.29 :<br /><br /><ul class="disc"><li>Compatibility functions Get_Iter_At_Location and Get_Iter_At_Position were added to the package Gtk.Missed. </li><li>The functions provide backward compatibility to GTK 3.14 to 3.19 when the GTK interface was changed. </li><li>The implementation works with both earlier and later versions.</li></ul><br />Changes to this version 5.15 : <br /><br /><ul class="disc"><li>GNAT Studio Community 2021 bugs worked around; </li><li>GTK 3.24.x support</li></ul><br /><br />See <a href="http://www.dmitry-kazakov.de/ada/gtkada_contributions.htm" target="_blank" title="GtkAda contributions">Dmitry&rsquo;s Web page</a> for details<br /><br />Download from <a href="https://sourceforge.net/projects/gtkadacontributions/files/latest/download " target="_blank" title="GtkAda contributions">SourceForge</a><br />Download source <a href="http://www.dmitry-kazakov.de/ada/gtkada_contributions_3_30.tgz" target="_blank" title="gtkada_contributions_3_30.tgz" download="http://www.dmitry-kazakov.de/ada/gtkada_contributions_3_30.tgz">gtkada_contributions_3_30.tgz</a> from <a href="http://www.dmitry-kazakov.de/ada/gtkada_contributions.htm" target="_blank" title="GtkAda contributions">Dmitry&rsquo;s Web</a><br /><br /><br /><br />&copy; dmitry-kazakov<br />GPL-2.0-or-later<br /><br /><br /><span class="blog-read-more"><a href="files/24b816fa2b7025a7192910a635992334-69.php"> Read More…</a></span><p class="blog-entry-tags">Tags: <a href="files/tag-gtk.php" title="GTK" rel="tag">GTK</a></p></div></div><div id="unique-entry-id-68" class="blog-entry"><h1 class="blog-entry-title"><a href="files/e0fbf66e17d4118737c3726106d77511-68.php" class="blog-permalink">Fuzzy sets library v5.15</a></h1><div class="blog-entry-date">2022-04-17 Filed in: <span class="blog-entry-category"><a href="files/category-framework.php">Framework</a></span></div><div class="blog-entry-body"><br />Changes to this version 5.15 : <br /><br /><ul class="disc"><li>GNAT Studio Community 2021 bugs worked around; </li><li>GTK 3.24.x support</li></ul><br /><br />See <a href="http://www.dmitry-kazakov.de/ada/fuzzy.htm" target="_blank" title="Fuzzy sets for Ada">Dmitry&rsquo;s Web page</a> for details<br /><br />Download from <a href="https://sourceforge.net/projects/fuzzysetsforada/files/latest/download " target="_blank" title="Fuzzy sets for Ada">SourceForge</a><br />Download source <a href="http://www.dmitry-kazakov.de/ada/fuzzy_5_15.tgz" target="_blank" title="components_4_61.tgz" download="http://www.dmitry-kazakov.de/ada/fuzzy_5_15.tgz">fuzzy_5_15.tgz</a> from <a href="http://www.dmitry-kazakov.de/ada/fuzzy.htm" target="_blank" title="Fuzzy sets for Ada">Dmitry&rsquo;s Web</a><br /><br /><br /><br />&copy; dmitry-kazakov<br />GPL-2.0-or-later<br /><br /><span class="blog-read-more"><a href="files/e0fbf66e17d4118737c3726106d77511-68.php"> Read More…</a></span><p class="blog-entry-tags">Tags: <a href="files/tag-ml.php" title="ML" rel="tag">ML</a></p></div></div></div>
								
							</section>
